 0.74);\"><li style=\"margin: 0px 0px 0.8em; padding: 0px 0px 0px 5px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: inherit;\">The grade increase exam for students who have failed one or two subjects will be held on&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: 600; font-family: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline;\">Ashoj 6 and 7.</span></li></ul><ul style=\"margin: 1.65em 0px 1.65em 35px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-size: 19px; font-family: ff-more-web-pro, &quot;PT Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; list-style: none; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.74);\"><li style=\"margin: 0px 0px 0.8em; padding: 0px 0px 0px 5px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: inherit;\">Students who have failed in more than two subjects will have to wait until next year to retake the exam.</li></ul>Grade 12 Results Details 2080 – NEB<br>Comparison between 2079 and 2080 +2 Results-NEB Notice<br>The results are a mixed bag, with some positive trends and some areas for improvement. The increase in the number of students who have secured an A+ is a good sign, and it suggests that the quality of education in Nepal is improving.<br>However, the high number of students who have failed the exam is a cause for concern. The NEB needs to take steps to improve the quality of education so that more students can succeed in the +2 Exam.</h6><figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\" style=\"margin: 40px auto; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-size: 19px; font-family: ff-more-web-pro, &quot;PT Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.74);\"></figure><figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\" style=\"margin: 40px auto; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-size: 19px; font-family: ff-more-web-pro, &quot;PT Serif&quot;, Georgia, serif; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.74);\"></figure><figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\" style=\"margin: 40px auto; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: basel